From 55de4c2893d764fd28c1af880e04e854907da34b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Michal=20Koutn=C3=BD?= <mkoutny@suse.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Mar 2025 18:04:34 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] sched: Remove unneeed macro wrap
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

References: bsc#1234634 (Scheduler functional and performance backports SL-16.1)
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
Git-commit: e285313f0848157cc3c6827d233a2510167b50cf

rt_entity_is_task has split definitions based on CONFIG_RT_GROUP_SCHED,
therefore we can use it always. No functional change intended.

Signed-off-by: Michal Koutný <mkoutny@suse.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20250310170442.504716-3-mkoutny@suse.com
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 kernel/sched/rt.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/rt.c b/kernel/sched/rt.c
index 86a661707a12..3db9436b85c3 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/rt.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/rt.c
@@ -1256,11 +1256,9 @@ static void __delist_rt_entity(struct sched_rt_entity *rt_se, struct rt_prio_arr
 static inline struct sched_statistics *
 __schedstats_from_rt_se(struct sched_rt_entity *rt_se)
 {
-#ifdef CONFIG_RT_GROUP_SCHED
 	/* schedstats is not supported for rt group. */
 	if (!rt_entity_is_task(rt_se))
 		return NULL;
-#endif
 
 	return &rt_task_of(rt_se)->stats;
 }
